  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations. In the United States, key AML legislation includes the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Implement compliance programs\n2. Report suspicious transactions\n3. Conduct customer due diligence\n4. Maintain transaction records\n5. Verify customer identities\n\nInternationally, the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) sets global standards for combating money laundering and terrorist financing.",
